ABUJA- PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has sent the name of Dr Kingsley Isitua Obiorah, the current Alternate Executive Director in the International Monetary Fund (IMF) In Washington DC, United States of America, to the Senate for confirmation as Deputy Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria. In a letter to President of the Senate, Ahmad Ibrahim Lawan, President Buhari said the nomination was in accordance with the provision of Section 8(1) (2) of the Central Bank of Nigeria (Establishment) Act 2007. Dr Obiora, upon confirmation by the Senate, replaces Dr Joseph Nnanna, who retires on February 2, 2020. Dr Obiora according to a statement by the Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Chief Femi Adesina, holds a Bachelor’s degree in Economics and Statistics from the University of Benin, a Masters in Economics from the University of Ibadan, and a Doctorate in Monetary and International Economics, also from the University of Ibadan. “He is currently an Alternate Executive Director in the International Monetary Fund (IMF) In Washington DC, United States of America,” Adesina said. Vanguard ABUJA-President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the names of non-executive members for the board of the Central Bank of Nigeria, CBN. April 12, 2017 In "News" The Presidency has urged the Senate to lift the embargo on confirmation of nominees sent to it by President Muhammadu Buhari. January 9, 2018 In "News" PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has written the Senate, seeking for the screening and subsequent confirmation of former Military governor of Old Oyo State, Major- General Paul Tarfa, retd as the Chairman of the North East Development Commission, NEDC. January 16, 2019 In "News"